org.j2free.util
Class Global

java.lang.Object
  org.j2free.util.Global

@ThreadSafe
public class Global
extends java.lang.Object

Basically, Global is just a static ConcurrentHashMap for storing and getting values by key. Ergo, javadocs copied from ConcurrentHashMap impl.

put

public static java.lang.Object put(java.lang.String key,

Maps the specified key to the specified value in this table. Neither the key nor the value can be null.

The value can be retrieved by calling the get method with a key that is equal to the original key.

Parameters:
key - the table key.
value - the value.
Returns:
the previous value of the specified key in this table, or null if it did not have one.
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the key or value is null.

putIfAbsent

public static java.lang.Object putIfAbsent(java.lang.String key,
                                           java.lang.Object value)
If the specified key is not already associated with a value, associate it with the given value. This is equivalent to 
  if (!map.containsKey(key))
      return map.put(key, value);
  else
      return map.get(key);
Except that the action is performed atomically.

Parameters:
key - key with which the specified value is to be associated.
value - value to be associated with the specified key.
Returns:
previous value associated with specified key, or null if there was no mapping for key.
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the specified key or value is null.

public static void clear()

remove

public static java.lang.Object remove(java.lang.String key)
Removes the key (and its corresponding value) from this table. This method does nothing if the key is not in the table.

Parameters:
key - the key that needs to be removed.
Returns:
the value to which the key had been mapped in this table, or null if the key did not have a mapping.
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the key is null.

remove

public static boolean remove(java.lang.String key,
                             java.lang.Object value)
Remove entry for key only if currently mapped to given value. Acts as 
  if (map.get(key).equals(value)) {
      map.remove(key);
      return true;
  } else return false;
except that the action is performed atomically.

Parameters:
key - key with which the specified value is associated.
value - value associated with the specified key.
Returns:
true if the value was removed
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the specified key is null.

replace

public static java.lang.Object replace(java.lang.String key,
                                       java.lang.Object value)
Replace entry for key only if currently mapped to some value. Acts as 
  if ((map.containsKey(key)) {
      return map.put(key, value);
  } else return null;
except that the action is performed atomically.

Parameters:
key - key with which the specified value is associated.
value - value to be associated with the specified key.
Returns:
previous value associated with specified key, or null if there was no mapping for key.
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the specified key or value is null.

replace

public static boolean replace(java.lang.String key,
                              java.lang.Object oldValue,
                              java.lang.Object newValue)
Replace entry for key only if currently mapped to given value. Acts as 
  if (map.get(key).equals(oldValue)) {
      map.put(key, newValue);
      return true;
  } else return false;
except that the action is performed atomically.

Parameters:
key - key with which the specified value is associated.
oldValue - value expected to be associated with the specified key.
newValue - value to be associated with the specified key.
Returns:
true if the value was replaced
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the specified key or values are null.
